Beacon Investment Advisory Services Inc. Continues to Hold Stake in Monsanto Company (NYSE:MON)

Posted by Dan Jones on Jul 23rd, 2017 // No Comments 

Beacon Investment Advisory Services Inc. held its position in Monsanto Company (NYSE:MON) during the first quarter, according to its most recent filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC). The firm owned 2,790 shares of the basic materials company’s stock at the end of the first quarter. Beacon Investment Advisory Services Inc.’s holdings in Monsanto were worth $316,000 at the end of the most recent reporting period. 
A number of other hedge funds and other institutional investors have also bought and sold shares of MON. Flossbach Von Storch AG boosted its position in shares of Monsanto by 33.9% in the first quarter. Flossbach Von Storch AG now owns 4,089,400 shares of the basic materials company’s stock worth $462,920,000 after buying an additional 1,034,400 shares in the last quarter. Norges Bank purchased a new position in shares of Monsanto during the fourth quarter worth approximately $406,735,000. UBS Asset Management Americas Inc. boosted its position in shares of Monsanto by 55.2% in the first quarter. UBS Asset Management Americas Inc. now owns 2,181,090 shares of the basic materials company’s stock worth $246,899,000 after buying an additional 775,520 shares in the last quarter. Legal & General Group Plc boosted its position in shares of Monsanto by 7.2% in the first quarter. Legal & General Group Plc now owns 2,124,147 shares of the basic materials company’s stock worth $240,459,000 after buying an additional 143,057 shares in the last quarter. Finally, Swiss National Bank boosted its position in shares of Monsanto by 25.6% in the first quarter. Swiss National Bank now owns 1,676,066 shares of the basic materials company’s stock worth $189,731,000 after buying an additional 341,400 shares in the last quarter. 74.87% of the stock is currently owned by institutional investors and hedge funds. 




Monsanto Company (MON) opened at 117.38 on Friday. Monsanto Company has a 12-month low of $97.35 and a 12-month high of $118.97. The stock has a 50 day moving average price of $117.61 and a 200-day moving average price of $114.05. The stock has a market capitalization of $51.57 billion, a PE ratio of 25.35 and a beta of 1.08. 


 Get Monsanto Company alerts:



Monsanto (NYSE:MON) last issued its earnings results on Wednesday, June 28th. The basic materials company reported $1.93 earnings per share (EPS) for the quarter, topping the Thomson Reuters’ consensus estimate of $1.74 by $0.19. Monsanto had a return on equity of 45.26% and a net margin of 14.11%. The firm had revenue of $4.23 billion for the quarter, compared to analysts’ expectations of $4.18 billion. During the same period in the previous year, the firm posted $2.17 earnings per share. The business’s revenue was up 1.0% compared to the same quarter last year. On average, equities analysts anticipate that Monsanto Company will post $4.89 earnings per share for the current fiscal year. 
The company also recently announced a quarterly dividend, which will be paid on Friday, July 28th. Stockholders of record on Friday, July 7th will be issued a $0.54 dividend. The ex-dividend date is Wednesday, July 5th. This represents a $2.16 annualized dividend and a dividend yield of 1.84%. Monsanto’s dividend payout ratio (DPR) is 46.75%. 
WARNING: “Beacon Investment Advisory Services Inc. Continues to Hold Stake in Monsanto Company (NYSE:MON)” was published by BNB Daily and is the sole property of of BNB Daily. If you are reading this article on another publication, it was stolen and reposted in violation of United States & international copyright laws. The correct version of this article can be viewed at https://www.baseball-news-blog.com/2017/07/23/beacon-investment-advisory-services-inc-has-316000-stake-in-monsanto-company-nysemon-updated.html. 
MON has been the topic of a number of recent research reports. Vetr cut Monsanto from a “buy” rating to a “hold” rating and set a $118.00 price target on the stock. in a research report on Monday, March 27th. Jefferies Group LLC reiterated a “buy” rating and set a $128.00 price objective on shares of Monsanto in a research note on Tuesday, March 28th. Royal Bank Of Canada reiterated a “hold” rating and set a $118.00 price objective on shares of Monsanto in a research note on Tuesday, March 28th. BMO Capital Markets reiterated a “buy” rating and set a $128.00 price objective on shares of Monsanto in a research note on Wednesday, April 5th. Finally, Citigroup Inc. reiterated a “neutral” rating and set a $125.00 price objective (up from $122.00) on shares of Monsanto in a research note on Friday, April 14th. Two investment analysts have rated the stock with a sell rating, ten have given a hold rating and nine have assigned a buy rating to the company. Monsanto presently has a consensus rating of “Hold” and an average price target of $123.15.
In other news, EVP Kerry J. Preete sold 11,346 shares of Monsanto stock in a transaction dated Wednesday, May 3rd. The stock was sold at an average price of $116.86, for a total value of $1,325,893.56. Following the sale, the executive vice president now directly owns 39,258 shares of the company’s stock, valued at $4,587,689.88. The sale was disclosed in a legal filing with the Securities & Exchange Commission, which is available at the SEC website. Also, SVP Janet M. Holloway sold 7,423 shares of Monsanto stock in a transaction dated Tuesday, June 13th. The stock was sold at an average price of $118.00, for a total value of $875,914.00. Following the completion of the sale, the senior vice president now directly owns 33,645 shares in the company, valued at $3,970,110. The disclosure for this sale can be found here. Insiders sold 85,816 shares of company stock worth $10,117,174 over the last ninety days. Insiders own 0.79% of the company’s stock. 
About Monsanto
Monsanto Company (Monsanto), along with its subsidiaries, is a provider of agricultural products for farmers. The Company provides seeds, biotechnology trait products, herbicides and digital agriculture tools to farmers. The Company operates through two segments: Seeds and Genomics, and Agricultural Productivity. 

 
